    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302950">Figure 50</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302950" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302950" filename="../figg13/G1302950.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 50. Auxiliary Drive Gear Assembly Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Straighten the lock tangs, and remove four bolts and two bearing retainers from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302951">Figure 51</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302951" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302951" filename="../figg13/G1302951.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. Remove Bolts and Bearing Retainers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the mainshaft rear, located in the auxiliary drive gear bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302952">Figure 52</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302952" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302952" filename="../figg13/G1302952.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Remove Snap Ring From Mainshaft Rear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With two screwdrivers, pry the auxiliary gear off the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302953">Figure 53</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302953" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302953" filename="../figg13/G1302953.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Pry Auxiliary Gear Off Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
